# Vowel Checker

## Author
Jeremiah E. Ochepo

## Code Description
This Python script checks the occurrences of vowels (a, e, i, o, u, y) in a given plaintext file. It provides a count of each vowel found in a case-insensitive manner.

## Last Updated Date
7/03/19

## How to Use
1. Run the script in a Python environment.
2. Enter the name of the plaintext file when prompted.
3. The script will display the content of the file, its length, and the count of each vowel present.

## File Structure
- `vowel_checker.py`: Main Python script.
- `text.txt`: Sample plaintext file. You can replace this with your own file.

## Note
If the entered file name is incorrect or the file does not exist, the script will display an error message.

Feel free to customize the code or use it as a template for your own projects!
